Matteo Guendouzi has joined Marseille on loan from Arsenal. The deal includes an obligation to buy next summer. Matteo Guendouzi has posted a farewell to Arsenal – though before his move to Olympique Marseille has been rubberstamped. The French midfielder, who spent last season on loan at Hertha Berlin, took to Instagram to announce the news with a lengthy statement. In a now-deleted message that appeared on both Twitter and Instagram, he wrote: “Thank you Arsenal. Thanks for everything